connections\n3. **Intelligent Backoff**: Round-robin aware backoff to optimize multi-endpoint retry\n4. **Configurable Retry Policies**: Different policies for immutable (repeatable) vs mutable (nonRepeatable) operations\n5. **Stream Retry Support**: Buffering allows stream retry while preserving order\n6. **Context-Based Timeout Control**: Leverages Go context for deadline propagation\n7. **Leader Awareness**: Optional WithRequireLeader metadata for consistency requirements\n\n## Implementation Details\n\nThe retry interceptor logic (client/v3/retry_interceptor.go lines 41-101 for unary):\n- Logs retry attempts with peer information\n- Handles authentication token refresh on auth errors\n- Respects context deadlines\n- Implements exponential backoff with jitter\n- Returns on context deadline or non-retryable errors\n\nThe stream retry logic (client/v3/retry_interceptor.go lines 234-258) in RecvMsg:\n- Only retries if previous receives failed (not after successful reception)\n- Buffers and resends client messages on reconnection\n- Maintains receive state to detect stream errors\n- Applies same backoff and retry policies as unary operations\n"
